summary:
Three Singapore stocks made announcements that may impact trading on Wednesday: 
AIMS AMP Capital Industrial Reit (AA Reit) launched a private placement exercise to raise S$50 million; 
Asian Micro Holdings issued shares for the right to buy four commercial units in Penang for RM1.6 million; 
UOL Group made a mandatory unconditional cash offer for all shares in Singapore Land at S$11.85 apiece.
